=== VERDICT (Stage B, this environment) ===
B1 (claude runs in a Linux container): PARTIAL — the CLI executes in-box (v2.1.185).
B2 (subscription billing path): CANNOT VALIDATE HERE.
  Why: this is a managed remote session. claude authenticates via an inherited
  file descriptor (CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN_FILE_DESCRIPTOR=4) + a managed proxy
  (ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL). fd 4 does NOT cross into a separate container (only 0-3
  present), so the turn fails with 'Authentication error'. No ANTHROPIC_API_KEY/
  CLAUDE_API_KEY is set, so it is NOT the API-billing path — there is simply no
  portable credential to carry in.

  On a real Docker host where a dev has run 'claude login', the OAuth credential is
  a mountable file (~/.claude/.credentials.json) and the in-box claude WOULD auth.
  B1/B2 must be run there, not in this managed sandbox.

  DESIGN FINDING: the box must hold the AGENT'S OWN model credential (unlike git
  creds, which stay on the host). This env demonstrates the clean pattern — broker
  the auth via a proxy + ephemeral token so the box never holds a reusable key.

=== Broker-validation attempt (authorized) — outcome: token not extractable here ===
Tried to forward this session's ephemeral token into the container (the broker's job).
Result: no forwardable credential is reachable in this managed environment —
  - ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL is the real api.anthropic.com (not a cred-injecting proxy)
  - the model OAuth token came via fd 4, was consumed at startup, fd now closed (pid 535: no fd 4)
  - no persisted credentials file (~/.claude/.credentials.json absent everywhere)
  - no apiKeyHelper configured (launcher-settings.json is hooks only)
  => the ephemeral token lives only in the parent process memory; not forwardable.
This REINFORCES the design: the ephemeral-token model isolates the credential well.
B1/B2 completion requires a host with a forwardable credential (a 'claude login' host
with persisted ~/.claude, or a host-side apiKeyHelper/broker).
